100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 2, 1926, the United States Senate passed the bill to create a Veterans Bureau, aimed at providing support for returning soldiers. Meanwhile, in Europe, tensions continued to rise as France and Germany engaged in heated discussions over reparations following World War I. In a notable development, the British government announced plans to address the ongoing strikes affecting coal production, which had significant implications for the economy.
